## Milestones

Numbered **M20.x** to extend the existing scheme. Human-approval gates (⛔) mirror
the existing public-release convention.

### M20.0 — Licensing & publish prerequisites  ⛔ (human approval)
**Goal:** Remove the hard blockers before any registry action.
- Choose and add a real license (root `LICENSE` + per-package `license` fields replacing `"SEE LICENSE (TBD)"`).
- Register/confirm org accounts: npm scope `@iap`, VS Code Marketplace publisher, OpenVSX namespace.
- Confirm public identities: `@iap/cli` bin `iap`, `@iap/mcp-server` bin `iap-mcp-server`, VS Code extension publisher id.
- **Exit:** LICENSE committed; `pnpm run check:names` still green; accounts provisioned; approver sign-off recorded.

### M20.1 — Self-contained MCP server package
**Goal:** Make the MCP server `npx`-able exactly as the CLI already is. *(The LSP is already bundled zero-dep by `extensions/vscode/build-server.mjs`; only the MCP server remains.)*
- Add `tools/packaging/build-mcp.mjs` mirroring `tools/packaging/build-cli.mjs` (esbuild bundle + staged runtime assets, `bin`, **no** `workspace:*` deps).
- Produce `dist-pkg/mcp-server/` + tarball.
- Add a `smoke:mcp` script (mirror `smoke:cli`), wire into `verify`.
- *(Optional)* Generalize `build-server.mjs` into `tools/packaging/build-language-server.mjs` only if a standalone `@iap/language-server` npm publish is wanted for JetBrains/other LSP clients — not needed for VS Code/Cursor (bundled).
- **Exit:** In a clean dir, `npx <mcp-tarball>` runs `iap-mcp-server` and the stdio handshake responds, with zero workspace paths on disk.

### M20.2 — Publish npm packages (public)
**Goal:** `iap` CLI and MCP server resolvable from public npm.
- Set `publishConfig.access: public`; add `repository`/`homepage`/`bugs`; verify `files` allowlists.
- Publish `@iap/cli` and `@iap/mcp-server` (bundled variant from M20.1) at `0.1.0`.
- *(Optional)* publish standalone `@iap/language-server` only if the JetBrains/other-LSP path is in scope.
- **Exit:** `npm i -g @iap/cli` gives a working `iap`; `npx @iap/mcp-server` starts the server — on a machine with no repo checkout.

### M20.3 — VS Code Marketplace + OpenVSX publish
**Goal:** One-click install in VS Code AND Cursor/Windsurf. *(The `.vsix` is already fully self-contained — LSP + client bundled, 4-step offline smoke gate green — so this is now purely the publishing wrapper, not a bundling effort.)*
- Remove `private: true`; replace `"license": "SEE LICENSE (TBD)"`; add metadata: `icon`, `repository`, `keywords`, `galleryBanner` (categories already set), bundled `README`/`CHANGELOG`/`LICENSE`.
- Refresh the stale `iap.languageServer.path` setting description in `package.json` to match the new bundled-first resolution (README already correct).
- Keep the offline hand-built `.vsix` for internal use; add a `vsce publish` (Marketplace) + `ovsx publish` (OpenVSX) path.
- Publish to VS Code Marketplace and OpenVSX.
- **Exit:** Fresh VS Code installs via Marketplace; fresh Cursor installs via OpenVSX; opening `infrastructure.iap.yaml` yields diagnostics/hover/completion with **no** manual bin setup.

### M20.4 — Claude Code plugin
**Goal:** IaP installable as a full Claude Code plugin (MCP + commands).
- Create `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` bundling the `iap-mcp-server` MCP server (via published npm bin from M20.2) plus IaP slash commands (e.g. `/iap-author`, `/iap-validate`) and optionally a skill.
- Create a `marketplace.json` (own repo or shared) so `claude plugin marketplace add` + `claude plugin install iap` works.
- **Exit:** `claude plugin install iap` registers the MCP server; `iap_author`/`iap_validate` callable in a Claude Code session against packaged artifacts only.

### M20.5 — Ready-to-use MCP client configs + install docs
**Goal:** Zero-friction registration for every non-plugin client.
- Ship copy-paste configs / one-liners for Claude Desktop (`claude_desktop_config.json`), Cursor (`.cursor/mcp.json`), VS Code native MCP (`.vscode/mcp.json`), Windsurf, and `claude mcp add iap -- npx -y @iap/mcp-server`.
- Update `docs/guides/ide-integration.md` to reference **published** artifacts (npm bins, marketplace links) instead of monorepo source paths; add a JetBrains LSP-config snippet.
- **Exit:** Each documented snippet, used verbatim on a clean machine, connects the client to `iap-mcp-server` and lists the 5 tools.

### M20.6 — Real-client interop + release verification  ⛔ (human approval)
**Goal:** Prove it works in the intended fashion, not just in smoke tests.
- Interop matrix: actually connect Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code, Windsurf → verify `initialize`, `tools/list`, and one `iap_author` + one analysis call each.
- Confirm the trust boundary holds live (no deploy/mutation tool surfaces; `assertReadOnly` intact).
- Assemble a `docs/reports/` distribution-release record mirroring the M19.8 developer-preview report.
- **Exit:** Interop matrix all-green with evidence; `verify` green including new smokes; approver sign-off for the public release.

### M20.7 (optional / stretch) — VS Code in-editor assistant panel
**Goal:** Close the documented-but-missing assistant panel gap.
- Implement an MCP client in `extensions/vscode/extension.js` that drives `iap_author` + analysis tools in a panel (docs already promise this).
- **Exit:** Panel authors a doc from NL and shows per-field provenance inside VS Code.

